{{Infobox person | name = Arash Ferdowsi | image = Arash Ferdowsi 2014 (cropped).jpg | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1985|10|7}} | birth_place = [[Overland Park, Kansas]], US | nationality = American | occupation = Co-Founder, [[Dropbox (service)|Dropbox]] | net_worth = [[United States dollar|US$]]1.1 billion (April 2018)<ref>{{cite web |title=Dropbox Stock Pop Puts Kansas Native in Tech Billionaires Club|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2018-03-23/dropbox-stock-pop-puts-kansas-native-in-tech-billionaires-club|website=Forbes|accessdate=1 April 2018 }}</ref> | spouse = | children = | residence = | website = | signature = }}
'''Arash Ferdowsi''' ({{lang-fa|آرش فردوسی}}, born October 7, 1985) is an [[Iranian American|Iranian-American]] billionaire entrepreneur. He is the co-founder of [[Dropbox (service)|Dropbox]].<ref>[http://www.crunchbase.com/person/arash-ferdowsi Arash Ferdowsi | CrunchBase Profile]. Crunchbase.com. Retrieved on 2013-07-14.</ref>
==Early life and education== Ferdowsi was born in [[Overland Park, Kansas]], US on 7 October 1985, the son of Iranian immigrants Gholam Ferdowsi (b. 1950) and Tahmineh "Tammy" Faridazar (b. 1959). Ferdowsi's father, a mortgage broker, is a native of [[Tabriz]] in northwestern Iran.<ref>{{cite web|title=Blue Valley Northwest grad is a billionaire, thanks to the tech company he founded|url=http://www.kansascity.com/news/business/article206994599.html|publisher=The Kansas City Star|accessdate=3 April 2018|date=28 March 2018}}</ref> His parents met and married in 1984, while students at the [[University of Central Missouri]] and the [[University of Missouri–Kansas City]], respectively. They settled in the US following the 1979 [[Iranian Revolution]].
He attended [[Blue Valley Northwest High School]], a public high school in Overland Park, graduating first in his class in 2004.<ref>{{cite web|title=Meet the richest area native you’ve probably never heard of|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130308110306/http://www.kansascity.com/2013/02/09/4057711/meet-the-richest-area-native-youve.html|publisher=The Kansas City Star|accessdate=3 April 2018|date=9 February 2013}}</ref> Ferdowsi went on to study electrical engineering and computer science at the [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]] (MIT), dropping out of his program in his last year to focus on his business.<ref name="30under30_2011"/>
==Career== Ferdowsi launched [[Dropbox (service)|Dropbox]] in June 2007 with his business partner, [[Drew Houston]], at [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology]]. In September 2007, Ferdowsi moved his company to San Francisco and raised [[venture capital]] from [[Sequoia Capital]], [[Accel Partners]], [[Y Combinator (company)|Y Combinator]], and a handful of individual investors.<ref name="30under30_2011"/> In March 2018, Dropbox underwent an initial public offering, valuing the company at around USD 9.2 billion.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dropbox Priced at $21 a Share in I.P.O., Valuing Company at $9.2 Billion|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/03/22/business/dealbook/dropbox-ipo.html|publisher=New York Times|accessdate=6 April 2018|date=22 March 2018}}</ref>
From the company's establishment in June 2007 until October 2016, Ferdowsi served as the chief technology officer (CTO) of Dropbox.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dropbox appoints new CTO, Aditya Agarwal, takes over for cofounder Arash Ferdowsi|url=https://venturebeat.com/2016/10/13/dropbox-appoints-new-cto-aditya-agarwal-replacing-cofounder-arash-ferdowsi/|website=Venture Beat|accessdate=3 April 2018|date=13 October 2016}}</ref> He remains a member of Dropbox's management team and board of directors.<ref>{{cite web|title=About - Dropbox|url=https://www.dropbox.com/about|publisher=Dropbox|accessdate=3 April 2018}}</ref>
==Awards and highlights== *[[Inc. (magazine)|Inc. Magazine]] named Ferdowsi to its 2011 "30 Under 30" top entrepreneurs list.<ref name="30under30_2011">{{cite web|url=http://www.inc.com/30under30/2011/profile-drew-houston-and-arash-ferdowsi-founders-dropbox.html|title=Inc.com 30under30: Drew Houston and Arash Ferdowsi, Founders of Dropbox|last=Carter|first=Nicole|date=2011-06-27|work=Inc.com|publisher=Mansueto Ventures|accessdate=5 November 2011}}</ref> *[[Fortune (magazine)|Fortune Magazine]] named Ferdowsi to its 2011 "40 Under 40" list.<ref name="40under40_2011">{{cite web |url=http://money.cnn.com/galleries/2011/news/companies/1110/gallery.40_under_40.fortune/29.html |title=40 Under 40 - Drew Houston and Arash Ferdowsi |work=money.cnn.com |publisher=Fortune |accessdate=1 January 2012}}</ref> *[[TechCrunch]] awarded Ferdowsi a Crunchie for "Founder Of The Year".<ref name="crunchies">{{cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2014/02/10/dropboxs-cloud-storage-kings-drew-houston-and-arash-ferdowsi-win-founder-of-the-year-crunchie|title=Dropbox’s Cloud Storage Kings Drew Houston And Arash Ferdowsi Win Founder Of The Year Crunchie|last=Constine|first=Josh|date=2014-02-11|work=TechCrunch|publisher=TechCrunch|accessdate=22 February 2012}}</ref>
