'''Mamdouh Abbas''' (born 1946) is an [[Egypt]]ian [[businessman]]. He was appointed the [[Zamalek SC|Zamalek]] chairman twice. His first appointment stretched  from 2006 to 2008. He returned to the position for the second time when he was elected president of the club in May 2009. He resigned from Zamalek in early November over a contract dispute.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.wigan.vitalfootball.co.uk/article.asp?a=131146|title=Mamdouh Abbas Resigns from Zamalek {{!}} Vital Wigan Athletic|date=2008-11-08|work=Vital Wigan Athletic|access-date=2018-06-11|language=en}}</ref><ref>http://thedailynewsegypt.com/football/zamalek-president-urges-abbas-to-keep-pumping-money-dp1.html</ref>
He managed a wide range of business companies in which their capital ranged between 5 and 450 million EGP.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=225555754&privcapId=426375911|website=Bloomberg|accessdate=7 July 2017}}</ref>

